<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="14">
<bibRefCitation author="Okutani, O" journalOrPublisher="Venus" pageId="12" pageNumber="23" pagination="49 - 59" title="Two new hadal bivalves of the Family Thyasiridae from the convergent area of the Japan Trench." volume="58" year="1999">Okutani et al. (1999)</bibRefCitation>
placed their new, deep-water Japanese thyasirid species into the shallow-water genus 
<taxonomicName class="Bivalvia" family="Thyasiridae" genus="Maorithyas" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Maorithyas" order="Lucinida" pageId="3" pageNumber="14" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Maorithyas</taxonomicName>
Fleming, 1950. They chose the generic placement of 
<taxonomicName class="Bivalvia" family="Thyasiridae" genus="Maorithyas" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Maorithyas hadalis" order="Lucinida" pageId="3" pageNumber="14" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="hadalis">Maorithyas hadalis</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation author="Okutani, O" journalOrPublisher="Venus" pageId="12" pageNumber="23" pagination="49 - 59" title="Two new hadal bivalves of the Family Thyasiridae from the convergent area of the Japan Trench." volume="58" year="1999">Okutani et al., 1999</bibRefCitation>
based on the shallow posterior radial sulcus, and relatively heavy sculpture. The internal shell characteristics of 
<taxonomicName class="Bivalvia" family="Thyasiridae" genus="Maorithyas" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Maorithyas hadalis" order="Lucinida" pageId="3" pageNumber="14" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="hadalis">Maorithyas hadalis</taxonomicName>
(holotype, NSMT 71431), namely the periostracum, hinge fig, nymph and anterior adductor muscle scar place it outside of 
<taxonomicName class="Bivalvia" family="Thyasiridae" genus="Maorithyas" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Maorithyas" order="Lucinida" pageId="3" pageNumber="14" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Maorithyas</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName class="Bivalvia" family="Thyasiridae" genus="Wallerconcha" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Wallerconcha" order="Lucinida" pageId="3" pageNumber="14" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Wallerconcha</taxonomicName>
(Figure 6
<normalizedToken originalValue="A–H">A-H</normalizedToken>
). It potentially belongs in a new genus, but that description is outside the scope of this paper.
</paragraph>
